Randstad are proud to currently be partnering with a large State Government
Department in assisting to recruit for an AO7 Content Editor based on the
Northside of Brisbane.

The Department's Information Management (IM) Program requires the services of
an AO7 Content Editors to work as part of the SharePoint to Cloud project
team. This role primarily involves writing and adapting content from legacy
intranet and SharePoint sites to our modern enterprise Intranet and SharePoint
Online platform. The position also involves collaborating with SMEs and
coordinating and guiding content creation.

You will be responsible for:

  * Migrate content from current intranet/SharePoint to new platform. 
  * Review and adapt content with Content Owners to meet new standards. 
  * Coordinate content creation with intranet team, SMEs, and IT. 
  * Provide input for migration plan and Teamsite migration dates. 
  * Control old-to-new mapping based on new architecture design. 
  * Direct business on content clean-up tasks for Teamsites. 

** Skills and experience requirements: ** **   
  
**

  * Mandatory: 5+ years experience, SharePoint CMS proficiency, web writing/editing skills, content migration expertise, collaboration ability. 
  * Desirable: Intranet content development experience, IA understanding, agile project leadership, user training support, user acceptance testing management. 

What You'll Receive

  * $82 - $88 per/Hourly + super 
  * State government agency 
  * Flexible working conditions 
  * A dedicated Government Consultant 

How to apply

If you think that this is a role that you might be perfect for, please apply
now!

